        <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;Source Quadrature&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please enter a preferred source quadrature. Three values represent the quadrature for X, Y, Z (rectangular geometries), R, Theta, Z (cylidrical geometries), and R, Theta, Phi (spherical geometries). Line sources use only the first entry. Point sources do not use quadrature. Default values used by ZapMeNotQt are 10, 10, 10.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
